      "item_id": "faq-rejected-block",
      "category": "mining_troubleshooting",
      "title": "Why does my miner find a block that the node rejects?",
      "short_answer": "Most often it is a race-loss: another miner found a block first and your candidate now points at a stale parent. Less commonly it means your miner version is older than the consensus rules the node now enforces.",
