      "item_id": "faq-thread-count",
      "category": "mining_troubleshooting",
      "title": "Why are 64 threads slower than 16 threads?",
      "short_answer": "ConvergenceX is memory-bandwidth bound. Past a certain thread count, threads compete for the same memory bus and the per-thread useful work drops faster than the thread count rises. The optimum is usually 16 or 32 on consumer hardware and rarely much higher even on servers.",
